    <div class="article-body">
      <div class="container content-width">
        <p><em>Last updated: March 2026</em></p>

        <h2>Educational Purpose</h2>

        <p>
          The Fiduciary Health Guide provides educational and informational content at the intersection of behavioral health and significant wealth. The content on this site is designed to support informed decision-making by families and the professionals who serve them.
        </p>

        <h2>Not Professional Advice</h2>

        <p>
          Nothing on this website constitutes medical, clinical, legal, financial, or other professional advice. The information provided is educational in nature and should not be used as a substitute for consultation with qualified professionals in the relevant disciplines.
        </p>

        <p>
          Behavioral health decisions should be made in consultation with licensed clinical professionals. Legal decisions should be made in consultation with qualified legal counsel. Financial decisions should be made in consultation with qualified financial advisors. The Fiduciary Health Guide does not replace any of these professional relationships.
        </p>

        <h2>No Provider-Client Relationship</h2>

        <p>
          Use of this website, including submission of the Connect form, does not create a professional relationship of any kind. A professional engagement, if one results from initial contact, will be established through separate, explicit agreement with its own terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>

        <p>
          All content on this website — including text, design, and organization — is the intellectual property of the Fiduciary Health Guide unless otherwise noted. Content may be referenced and linked to freely. Reproduction of substantial portions of content requires prior written permission.
        </p>

        <h2>Accuracy and Currency</h2>

        <p>
          We endeavor to ensure that all content is accurate and current as of the date of publication. However, the fields of behavioral health, fiduciary law, and wealth management evolve continuously. Readers should verify current applicability of any information with qualified professionals.
        </p>

        <h2>External Links</h2>

        <p>
          This site may contain links to external resources. These links are provided for informational purposes. The Fiduciary Health Guide does not endorse, control, or assume responsibility for the content of external websites.
        </p>

        <h2>Crisis Resources</h2>

        <p>
          If you or someone you know is in immediate danger, contact emergency services (911 in the United States). For behavioral health crises, contact the 988 Suicide and Crisis Lifeline by calling or texting 988, or the SAMHSA National Helpline at 1-800-662-4357.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing Law</h2>

        <p>
          These terms are governed by applicable law. Any disputes arising from use of this site will be resolved in accordance with applicable jurisdictional requirements.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>

        <p>
          Questions about these terms may be directed through our <a href="/connect/">Connect</a> page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
